history.content:
As far as I can tell, all of the open seats in the class are reserved (with 63 open seats reserved for EECS/CS/NE/MSE majors, and the rest being reserved for no one).

Thus, I'm not sure why you're implying that the people who enroll into the class right now are of other majors.

To answer your general question, that is not inconsistent with what the enrollment procedures say: "Once Phase II is over.... Neither major status nor class standing will impact enrollment at this point." 

Although, there appears to have been a delay in implementing this, as per @1901, so I suppose that we're effectively still in Phase II in terms of registration priority, when EECS/CS majors do have priority.

children.subject: There are 51 seats that are "open" but reserved until TA support is confirmed (as per this page). Thus, they are effectively not open (hence my "reserved for no one", which I now realize is ambiguous: the reading is supposed to be that no one can get into those seats).
That's odd, schedule.berkeley.edu appears to be showing 118 open seats

history.content: How is it that people are able to enroll into CS 186 during the adjustment period but declared CS is still stuck on the waitlist eventhough they used phase 2 credits? This is in direct contradiction with what the enrollment procedures say. Will CS declared be given priority to get of the waitlist if they had to waitlist themselves during phase 2 (because they were not declared at that point?)
